    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-02T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-02T08:00:00-05:00" n="970"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d970">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 EW/9–245: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Alexander C. Kirk</persName>,
                        Political Adviser to the Supreme Allied Commander, Mediterranean Theater, to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caserta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-02T15:00:00+02:00"
                            >September 2, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 2—1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3489. Our British colleague has shown us a copy of draft peace treaty with Italy
                    prepared by FornOff.<note n="38" xml:id="d970fn1">See memorandum by the United
                        Kingdom Delegation to the Council of Foreign Ministers (C.F.M. (45) 3),
                        dated September 12, 1945, <ref target="frus1945v02#pg_135">vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 135</ref>.</note> We assume Department
                    has seen this document which in length is reminiscent of Treaty of Versailles.
                    Quick survey thereof indicates that it is very severe.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kirk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
